citations:
    citation-affc-cersei-i:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Cersei I"
            text_from_source: "I am the only true son he ever had."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Cersei Lannister. Opens AFFC at the moment Cersei is awakened by Ser Osmund Kettleblack to learn Tywin Lannister has been found dead in his privy, shot with a crossbow bolt. She goes to the Tower of the Hand where Qyburn is found and appointed to tend to Tywin's body. The body of Shae (Tyrion's whore) is also found in Tywin's bed, strangled with a golden chain; Cersei orders her body disposed of secretly. Jaime emerges from the hidden passage; Cersei asks him to be Hand, he refuses. Ser Boros Blount reports Tyrion has escaped his cell — the gaoler Rugen is missing, two guards found asleep. Key figures: Ser Osmund Kettleblack, Ser Osney Kettleblack, Ser Osfryd Kettleblack, Ser Boros Blount, Ser Meryn Trant, Kevan Lannister (present), Puckens and Shortear (guards), Jocelyn Swyft and Senelle (Cersei's maids). Qyburn introduced as a fallen maester who treated Jaime's stump. The gaoler Rugen identified as a Varys agent. Shae named and described."
